<db:section xml:id="details">
<db:title>Detailed Description</db:title>
<db:mediaobject>
<db:imageobject>
<db:imagedata fileref="images/qtquickcontrols2-slider.gif"/>
</db:imageobject>
</db:mediaobject>
<db:para>Slider is used to select a value by sliding a handle along a track.</db:para>
<db:para>In the example below, custom <db:link xlink:href="qml-qtquick-controls2-slider.xml#from-prop">from</db:link>, <db:link xlink:href="qml-qtquick-controls2-slider.xml#value-prop">value</db:link>, and <db:link xlink:href="qml-qtquick-controls2-slider.xml#to-prop">to</db:link> values are set:</db:para>
<db:programlisting language="cpp">Slider {
    from: 1
    value: 25
    to: 100
}
</db:programlisting>
<db:para>The <db:link xlink:href="qml-qtquick-controls2-slider.xml#position-prop">position</db:link> property is expressed as a fraction of the control's size, in the range <db:code>0.0 - 1.0</db:code>. The <db:link xlink:href="qml-qtquick-controls2-slider.xml#visualPosition-prop">visualPosition</db:link> property is the same, except that it is reversed in a <db:link xlink:href="qtquick-positioning-righttoleft.xml">right-to-left</db:link> application. The <db:link xlink:href="qml-qtquick-controls2-slider.xml#visualPosition-prop">visualPosition</db:link> is useful for positioning the handle when styling Slider. In the example above, <db:link xlink:href="qml-qtquick-controls2-slider.xml#visualPosition-prop">visualPosition</db:link> will be <db:code>0.24</db:code> in a left-to-right application, and <db:code>0.76</db:code> in a right-to-left application.</db:para>
